metadata.name: Zometric #12
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: Hashed Cities #23
metadata.description:
This token generates a deterministic set of minimal, abstract buildings of varying widths, heights, transparencies, and patterns, assembling a skyline view of your own unique imaginary city. Each city comes with its own randomized city day.

Each mint has a native setting (Day or Night) which combined with the current time of viewing influences real-time movements of celestial bodies in your mint, e.g. on a mint with the Day setting, the sun will only appear when viewed during the day. The piece will re-render every minute.

The individual strokes of this token feature some of my latest developments of an algorithm that generatively simulates the texture of print imperfections. They are randomized at each render to give it a unique character. Note that depending on the complexity of each mint, some renders may introduce a brief pause. The aesthetics are greatly inspired by plotter art of early computer artists such as 'City Painting' by Grace C. Hertlein.

Made in p5js
Created Nov 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Syzers #472
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

Â·Â·Â·Â· On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned Â·Â·Â·Â·

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

metadata.name: Traversal #7
metadata.description:
Traversal is the marriage of two simple geometric ideas: a set of somewhat unruly, intersecting diagonal shapes, and a minimally reduced corner perspective that gives them depth.

The depicted bodies are entirely feasible as a 3D scene, and yet this composition is all about illusion. The hatch fill creates a perception of light. The dithering on the faces produces a sense of material texture. The squiggly lines imitate freehand drawing. The spatial perspective itself is achieved through a purely two-dimensional algorithm of polygon intersections and line hiding.

The original medium of my compositions is the pen plotter, and Traversal is no exception. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. It contains two layers visible in Inkscape, so you can plot the light grey sketch lines with a different pen, or omit them altogether.

metadata.name: Bifurcations (straight lines) #5
metadata.description:
An line drawn on the screen until it bifurcates. The same is done for each new line, and so on. The color changes over the time, under the rules of five available color modes: random, complementary, grayscale, monochrome and boogie-woogie (red, yellow, blue, black and white, like in the Mondrian boogie-woogie paintings)

Press P to download a high resolution image, and Space to pause the animation.

metadata.name: Giza #70
metadata.description:
Tried to catch a poetic atmosphere working on this generative representation of the pyramids of Giza.
Built by thousands of humans during tens of years thousands years ago they're now generated in seconds with millions of dots by a javascript algorithm.
That's were knowledge has led us !

Features
 - Time: Day (probability 1/2) / Night (probability 1/2)
 - Mode: Dark (probability 5/6) / Light (probability 1/6)
 - Number of pyramids
 - Background dunes
 - Global ligthness
 - Sun/Moon shine
 - generative color palette

Only Javascript / No library used
